#	xOS/Linux: 	~/bash-conf
# 
# Setup: 
#	1. Clone my bash/vim conf repo:
#		[~]$ git clone ssh://browndom@browndomain.com/~/git/bash-conf.git
#	2. Link my bash/vim conf files:
#		[~]$ ln -s ~/bash-conf/bash_aliases .bash_aliases
#		[~]$ ln -s ~/bash-conf/vim .vim
#		[~]$ ln -s ~/bash-conf/vimrc .vimrc
#
# Making Changes:
#	1. Pull latest version:
#		[~/bash-conf]$ git pull		
#	3. Open conf file:
#		[~/bash-conf]$ vim bash_aliases
#	1. Before edit, backup this file (;s in vim). 
#      The script ";s" outputs a new file in the fmt:
#			bash_aliases_<date>_<time>_backup
#	2. Push
#		[~/bash-conf]$ git push
#
